From: Build fix
Subject: [PATCH] widgets: guard QTipLabel::styleSheetParentDestroyed with style_stylesheet

In Qt 6.11.1 the declaration of styleSheetParentDestroyed() in
qtooltip_p.h is guarded by #if QT_CONFIG(style_stylesheet), but the
definition in qtooltip.cpp is not. When qt6base is built without
stylesheet support the compiler fails with:

  error: no declaration matches 'void QTipLabel::styleSheetParentDestroyed()'

Wrap the definition in the same preprocessor guard as the declaration.

--- a/src/widgets/kernel/qtooltip.cpp
+++ b/src/widgets/kernel/qtooltip.cpp
@@ -377,6 +377,7 @@ bool QTipLabel::tipChanged(const QPoint &pos, const QString &text, QObject *o)
        return false;
 }

+#if QT_CONFIG(style_stylesheet)
 /** \internal
   Cleanup the _q_stylesheet_parent property.
  */
@@ -385,6 +386,7 @@ void QTipLabel::styleSheetParentDestroyed()
     setProperty("_q_stylesheet_parent", QVariant());
     styleSheetParent = nullptr;
 }
+#endif

 /*!
     Shows \a text as a tool tip, with the global position \a pos as
